'''Mî-koet Kûng-lî-fi Chhâ-fi''' (American Board of Commissioners for Foreign Missions, ABCFM) chhiòn-chhṳ̂n he '''Mî-koet Kûng-lî-chûng Hói-ngoi Chhòn-tho-phu''', kién-chhṳ̂n '''Mî-phu-fi''', he thi-yit-ke [[Mî-koet]] [[Kî-tuk-kau]] hói-ngoi chhòn-kau kî-kèu. 1810-ngièn, Mî-koet [[Mà-sat-chû-set-chû]] Vî-liâm-sṳ̂ ho̍k-yen ke yit-phî pit-ngia̍p-sâng thì-ngi sṳ̀n-li̍p, 1812-ngièn chang-sṳt chhóng-li̍p. 1961-ngièn lâu khì-thâ kî-kèu ha̍p-pìn sṳ̀n-li̍p Mî-koet Lièn-ha̍p Kî-tuk-kau-fi Chhâ-fi (United Church Board for World Ministries). 

Mî-phu-fi ke sṳ̀n-li̍p su-to liáu Thi-ngi-chhṳ thai-kok-siáng ke yáng-hióng, tet-to [[Kûng-lî-fi]], [[Chhòng-ló-fi]] (1812–1870), [[Mî-koet Kûi-chang-fi]] (1826–1857) tén kau-phai ke kî-chhṳ̀, heu-lòi Kûng-lî-fi yî-ngoi ke kau-phai liu̍k-sa thui-chhut. 

